    {
      "type": "contrast_example",
      "content": "In Poem 2, we see the form <span style='color: #e67e22;'>ませ (mase)</span>. This is the 'Imperative' form of 'masu'. However, when used in poetry addressed to a superior or in a prayer, it doesn't function as a harsh command. Instead, it functions as a **formal wish** or **supplication**. \n\n- **し (shi)**: Do/Make\n- **ませ (mase)**: [Please] do (Polite/Formal Wish)\n\nThis is logically equivalent to the Chinese '请' (qǐng) or '愿' (yuàn) used in formal contexts."
    },
